asbru-cm (5.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed: crash when creating a RDP connection
  * Fixed: wrong tooltip for session log numbers
  * Fixed: Perl script redundant execution
  * Fixed: dependency on dbus-x11 added in Debian package
  * Update split panes separator handling (Alberto Rinaudo)
  * Retrieve terminal method inside scripts
  * Support for FreeBSD login
  * Add option to change main window title with terminal title (Andrey Kuzmin)
  * Better access to the "Info" tab

 -- Ásbrú Project Team <contact@asbru-cm.net>  Fri, 19 Apr 2019 13:56:29 +0200

asbru-cm (5.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed: application crash on connection delete
  * Fixed: quote user/pass when calling xfreerdp
  * Fixed: split feature no longer inverts horizontal/vertical (V.Gouvalas)
  * Fixed: removed deprecated "have" function (Daniel Augustin)
  * Fixed: don't clobber key-accelerators not used by Ásbrú, pass them to
    terminal widget (Michael Postmann)
  * Fixed: do not re-open connections list when hidden when switching tabs
  * Fixed: canceling user input dialogs cause connection failure
  * Added option to auto hide main buttons bar (Luke F.)
  * Reduce height of macro buttons (Luke F.)
  * Improved group name semantics; append instead of prepend (V.Gouvalas)
  * Added "close disconnected terminals" option to terminal context menu
  * Changed default value for connection config "auto save" to ON
  * Included Ansible playbook for unattended installs (nomike)

 -- Ásbrú Project Team <contact@asbru-cm.net>  Mon, 23 Jul 2018 20:56:29 +0100

asbru-cm (5.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed: SSH advanced options
  * Fixed: segmentation fault on exit
  * Fixed: maximized window state not correctly saved
  * Added new keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+Shift+R) to restart a session
  * Added script to import connections from SuperPutty
  * Added dash sign (-) when the parent folder is empty
  * Changed terminal icons
  * Improved Debian packaging

